Here's a Java program that uses multithreading to calculate the factorial of a given integer n:

```java
import java.math.BigInteger;
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

public class FactorialMultithreaded {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws InterruptedException {
        int n = 20; // Change this value to compute the factorial of another number

        System.out.println("Factorial of " + n + " is: " + factorial(n));
    }

    private static BigInteger factorial(int n) throws InterruptedException {
        int numOfThreads = Runtime.getRuntime().availableProcessors();
        List<FactorialThread> threads = new ArrayList<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < numOfThreads; i++) {
            int from = (n / numOfThreads) * i + 1;
            int to = (i == numOfThreads - 1) ? n : (n / numOfThreads) * (i + 1);
            FactorialThread thread = new FactorialThread(from, to);
            threads.add(thread);
            thread.start();
        }

        BigInteger result = BigInteger.ONE;
        for (FactorialThread thread : threads) {
            thread.join();
            result = result.multiply(thread.getResult());
        }

        return result;
    }

    private static class FactorialThread extends Thread {
        private final int from;
        private final int to;
        private BigInteger result;

        public FactorialThread(int from, int to) {
            this.from = from;
            this.to = to;
        }

        @Override
        public void run() {
            result = BigInteger.ONE;
            for (int i = from; i <= to; i++) {
                result = result.multiply(BigInteger.valueOf(i));
            }
        }

        public BigInteger getResult() {
            return result;
        }
    }
}
```

This program calculates the factorial of a given integer `n` using multiple threads. It divides the task among `numOfThreads`, which is determined by the number of available processors in the system.

Each thread calculates a partial factorial for a specific range, and then the main thread combines the results at the end to get the final result.

