java SimpleHttpServer <IP Address> <Port Number> <Static File Directory>
```

Replace `<IP Address>`, `<Port Number>`, and `<Static File Directory>` with the desired values.

Here is a simple implementation of a chat server using Java sockets:

```java
import java.io.*;
import java.net.*;
import java.util.*;

public class ChatServer {
    private static final int PORT = 1234;
    private static HashSet<String> names = new HashSet<String>();
    private static HashSet<PrintWriter> writers = new HashSet<PrintWriter>();

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        System.out.println("The chat server is running.");
        ServerSocket listener = new ServerSocket(PORT);
        try {
            while (true) {
                new Handler(listener.accept()).start();
            }
        } finally {
            listener.close();
        }
    }

    private static class Handler extends Thread {
        private String name;
        private Socket socket;
        private BufferedReader in;
        private PrintWriter out;

        public Handler(Socket socket) {
            this.socket = socket;
        }

        public void run() {
            try {
                in = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(
                    socket.getInputStream()));
                out = new PrintWriter(socket.getOutputStream(), true);

                while (true) {
                    out.println("SUBMITNAME");
                    name = in.readLine();
                    if (name == null) {
                        return;
                    }
                    synchronized (names) {
                        if (!names.contains(name)) {
                            names.add(name);
                            break;
                        }
                    }
                }

                out.println("NAMEACCEPTED");
                writers.add(out);

                while (true) {
                    String input = in.readLine();
                    if (input == null) {
                        return;
                    }
                    for (PrintWriter writer : writers) {
                        writer.println("MESSAGE " + name + ": " + input);
                    }
                }
            } catch (IOException e) {
                System.out.println(e);
            } finally {
                if (name != null) {
                    names.remove(name);
                }
                if (out != null) {
                    writers.remove(out);
                }
                try {
                    socket.close();
                } catch (IOException e) {}
            }
        }
    }
}
```

This program creates a chat server that listens to port 1234. When a client connects, the server requests a unique screen name by sending the client the text "SUBMITNAME", and keeps requesting until it receives a unique name.

After a client submits a unique name, the server acknowledges with "NAMEACCEPTED". Then it broadcasts incoming messages from this client to all other clients, prepending a message identifier string "MESSAGE" and the identity of the sender.

Client connections are managed in a separate thread so multiple clients can connect simultaneously.

import java.util.Scanner;

public class FactorialCalculator {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("Enter a positive integer: ");

        // Validate user input
        while (!scanner.hasNextInt()) {
            System.out.println("Invalid input. Please enter a positive integer.");
            scanner.next();
        }

        int num = scanner.nextInt();

        // Ensure the input is a positive integer
        while (num < 0) {
            System.out.println("Invalid input. Please enter a positive integer.");
            num = scanner.nextInt();
        }

        // Calculate factorial using recursion
        long result = factorial(num);
        System.out.printf("Factorial of %d is: %d%n", num, result);
    }

    // Recursive method to calculate factorial
    private static long factorial(int n) {
        if (n == 0 || n == 1) {
            return 1;
        } else {
            return n * factorial(n - 1);
        }
    }
}

