Here's a simple Golang program that simulates a producer-consumer scenario using goroutines and channels. The producer generates random numbers, while the consumer calculates their average.

```go
package main

import (
	"fmt"
	"math/rand"
	"sync"
	"time"
)

const (
	numProducers = 5
	numConsumers = 2
	bufferSize   = 10
)

func main() {
	rand.Seed(time.Now().UnixNano())

	dataChannel := make(chan int, bufferSize)
	var wg sync.WaitGroup

	for i := 0; i < numProducers; i++ {
		wg.Add(1)
		go func(id int) {
			defer wg.Done()
			producer(dataChannel, id)
		}(i)
	}

	for i := 0; i < numConsumers; i++ {
		wg.Add(1)
		go func(id int) {
			defer wg.Done()
			consumer(dataChannel, id)
		}(i)
	}

	wg.Wait()
	close(dataChannel)
	fmt.Println("All producers and consumers have finished.")
}

func producer(data chan<- int, id int) {
	for i := 0; i < 10; i++ {
		num := rand.Intn(100)
		fmt.Printf("Producer %d generated number: %d\n", id, num)
		data <- num
		time.Sleep(time.Duration(rand.Intn(500)) * time.Millisecond)
	}
}

func consumer(data <-chan int, id int) {
	count := 0
	sum := 0
	for num := range data {
		fmt.Printf("Consumer %d received number: %d\n", id, num)
		sum += num
		count++
		if count == (numProducers * 10) / numConsumers {
			break
		}
	}
	average := float64(sum) / float64(count)
	fmt.Printf("Consumer %d calculated average: %.2f\n", id, average)
}
```

This program creates a fixed number of producers and consumers using goroutines. The producer generates random numbers and sends them to the data channel. The consumer reads from the data channel and calculates the average of the received numbers.

You can adjust the `numProducers`, `numConsumers`, and `bufferSize` constants to change the number of producers, consumers, and the size of the buffer for the data channel.

Here's a Java program that calculates the factorial of a number using recursion:

```java
import java.util.Scanner;

public class FactorialRecursion {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
        System.out.print("Enter a non-negative integer: ");
        int n = scanner.nextInt();

        if (n < 0) {
            System.out.println("Invalid input. Please enter a non-negative integer.");
        } else {
            long result = factorial(n);
            System.out.printf("The factorial of %d is: %d%n", n, result);
        }
    }

    private static long factorial(int n) {
        if (n == 0 || n == 1) {
            return 1;
        } else {
            return n * factorial(n - 1);
        }
    }
}
