Here is a JavaScript function that finds the most frequent element in an array:

```javascript
function findMostFrequent(arr) {
    if (!Array.isArray(arr)) {
        throw new TypeError('The given value is not an array');
    }

    var frequency = {};  // array of frequency.
    var maxFreq = 0;  // holds the max frequency.
    var result;   // holds the max frequency element.
    for(var i in arr) {
        frequency[arr[i]]=(frequency[arr[i]] || 0)+1; // increment frequency.

        if(frequency[arr[i]] > maxFreq) { 
            maxFreq = frequency[arr[i]];  // update max frequency.
            result = arr[i];      // update the result.
        }
    }

    return result;
}
```

This function uses an object to count the frequency of each element in the array. It then iterates over the array and updates the maximum frequency and the most frequent element whenever it finds a more frequent element.

To create a Node.js application that reads a directory's contents and calculates the total size of all files within it, you can use the `fs` module to read the directory and get file stats. Here's an example implementation:

